msgSnippet: If you look in the Files area for this group: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Read_Alphabet/files/ You ll see a file called Quickscript_alfabet.png . It s an
messageBody:
If you look in the Files area for this group:
http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Read_Alphabet/files/

You'll see a file called "Quickscript_alfabet.png". It's an image that
maps the QS alphabet to Dutch. There's no accompanying text, so I can
only hope that it's a fairly complete mapping.

I'm one of those who is designing a QS font, but working on it quite
slowly. If you produce something of MA-design quality, we'd all love
to see it.

Ted


On Dec 4, 2007 7:55 AM, Robin Franzen <robee_771@...> wrote:
>
>
> Hi my name is Robin. I stumbled over this source via the internet. I got very interested in this alphabet
> and especially the aspect of saving space. I'm currently looking for a subject for my MA-project in graphic design.
> I have two questions:
> – I would very much get intouch with people who have designed fonts using this alphabet.
> – Has there been any adaptation of the alphabet for scandinavian languages, such as swedish, norwegian or danish?
>
> Hopefully,
> Rob
